s, animals. So I am just like St. Francis. Where did this idea come from? From a story in the book, The Little Flowers of St Francis. &nbsp;The story tells about an episode when the friars were walking back to Assisi and Francis saw a flock of birds on the side of the road. He walked among them, and they stayed there as if listening to him and only flying off when he said they could leave.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Giottos famous painting in the Basilica of Assisi depicts this.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','[FSEN] Franciscan Spirituality','','inherit','closed','closed','','95-revision-v1','','','2020-09-28 20:59:12','2020-09-29 00:59:12','',95,'http://local.trilliumregionalofs.com/index.php/2020/09/28/95-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(375,1,'2020-09-29 12:27:12','2020-09-29 16:27:12','<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1>Who We Are</h1>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Secular Franciscans are people who seek to follow Jesus in the footsteps of St. Francis, who made Christ the inspiration and the centre of his life. Living the Gospel 24-7 is our goal. From the Gospel to LIFE and from life to the GOSPEL. Is this possible? By the grace of God  St. Francis did it. AND he wrote a rule to help us follow Jesus this closely! You are not here by chance. Perhaps you have been called here? YOU are WELCOME here! Please visit all our pages and links and contact us.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>THE ORDER</strong>The worldwide<a href=\"http://www.ciofs.org/portal\"><strong>Secular Franciscan Order</strong></a>is approved by the Church. It has a<a href=\"https://ofstrilliumregion.weebly.com/formation-resources.html\"><strong>Rule</strong></a>of life and is not simply a pious society or association. As a lay order, we are not called to leave the world, but to transform it.Our Order has fraternities at the Local, Regional, National and International levels with duly e