:31:50','2020-10-14 13:31:50','<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1>A Dwelling Place</h1> \n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/A-Dwelling-Place.jpg\" style=\"float:left;padding-right:20px;\">\nAn important aspect of Franciscan Spirituality is to make room for God in our lives. In the Early Rule of 1221 for the Friars, Francis wrote these words: \n<br>\n<br>\nWithin our hearts we must make a home and dwelling place for God our Lord, the almighty Father, the Son and Holy Spirit. God is always near us, and in prayer we consciously think of God, we place ourselves in his presence. Francis tells us it is the opposite. We must make a presence - a home for God in our hearts so that we may carry him with us always.\"\n<br>\n<br>\nThere is an interesting reflection on making a home, a dwelling place for God. \n<br>\n<br>\nLuke 11:24-26 When the unclean spirit has gone out of a man, he passes through waterless places seeking rest; and finding none he says, `I will return to my house from which I came.\' And when he comes he finds it swept and put in order. Then he goes and brings seven other spirits more evil than himself, and they enter and dwell there; and the last state of that man becomes worse than the first.\n<br>\n<br>\nFrancis reminds us that It is not good enough to just banish evil thoughts and habits, to hate ones body with its vice as he says in his Letter to all the Faithful. It isnt sufficient to just clean ones house. We must also fill the void with God who is the source of all that is good and upright. We must make a home and dwelling place for God.\n<br>\n<br>\nFranciscan Spirituality is centred on three key mysteries of our Faith. These mysteries Francis meditated on frequently. They are the Incarnation, the Paschal Mystery and the Eucharist. We might say the crib, the cross and the Mass.\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','[ADEN] A Dwelling Place','','inherit','closed','closed','','110-revision-v1','','','2020-10-14 09:31:50','2020-10-14 13:31:50','',110,'http://local.trilliumregionalofs.com/index.php/2020/10/14/110-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(671,1,'2020-10-14 10:41:27','2020-10-14 14:41:27','<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1>Memorial Wall</h1>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<strong><font color=\"#24678d\">CAPUCHINS OF CENTRAL CANADA</font></strong><br>\nMacDonald, Father Joseph, OFM, Cap. Deceased July 10th, 2018<br><br>\n<strong><font color=\"#24678d\">SACRED HEART - GUELPH</font></strong><br>\nBreese, Mary, ofs, Deceased March 12th 2019<br>\nHebert, Marc, ofs, professed May 2013 Deceased October 22, 2019<br>\nRobbie, Pierette, ofs Deceased 2016<br><br>\n<strong><font color=\"#24678d\">HOLY ROSARY - BELLEVILLE</font></strong><br>\nBissette, Margaret, ofs Professed 1985, Deceased 2004<br>\nDalpee, Larry, ofs Deceased 2010<br>\nDoran, Paul, ofs, Deceased May 14, 2019<br>\nHaley, Ann, ofs, Professed 1992, Deceased 2007<br>\nHogan, Joe, Sr., ofs, Professed 1987, Deceased 2005<br>\nLang, Elizabeth, ofs, Deceased October 2019<br>\nMulvihill, Jean, ofs, Professed 1965, Deceased 2011<br>\nPope, Dorothy, ofs professed March 18, 1985, Deceased October 2018<br>\nTugnett, Margaret, ofs, Professed 1948, Deceased 2008<br><br>\n<strong><font color=\"#24678d\">IMMACULATE CONCEPTION - TORONTO</font></strong><br>\nBelllissimo, Angela, ofs, Professed 1971, Deceased 2009<br>\nCasulo, Salvatore, ofs, Deceased 2013<br>\nCianfarani, Maria, ofs, Professed 1980, Deceased 2012<br>\nRizzardo, Giulia, ofs, Professed 1990, Deceased 2011<br>\nSackley, Francis<br><br>\n<strong><font color=\"#24678d\">MARY QUEEN OF PEACE - CARLSRUHE</font></strong><br>\nAgombar, Bert, ofs, Professed 1999, Deceased 2007<br>\nCassidy, Robert, ofs, Deceased 2017<br>\nGrubb, Irvin, ofs, Professed 1983, Deceased 2007<br>\nGrubb, Monica, ofs, Professed 1983, deceased 2012<br>\nLammers, Maria, ofs, Professed 1976, Deceased 2010<br>\nScoles, Rev. James, ofs, Professed 2002, Deceased 2011<br>\nStojanov, Rose, ofs, Dec